cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY

This paper discusses the feasibility of using LTE network infrastructure and LTE-Uu air interface to provide ultra-reliable low latency communications (URLLC) for vehicular traffic and public safety. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
